<tr><td align=left valign=top>Swordman:</td><td>The basic unit of the elven army, they are great 
to take many damages in order to save the most expensive units.  Swordmen should constitute 
the major part of your army and will eventually become your best line of defense.</td></tr> 
 
<tr><td align=left valign=top>Lanceman:</td><td>The major strength of this unit is their ability 
to easily kill mounted units, beside this major strength of this unit is that it is cheap and 
can make deal enough damages before dying.</td></tr> 
 
<tr><td align=left valign=top>Caragous:</td><td>The elite melee elven unit, the Caragous are the 
best riders ever trained by the elves.  In great numbers these unit will quickly overwhelm the 
battlefield, surround the ennemy charge and litterally annehilate their opponents.  Also 
calling the Birds of Justice, these extraordinary cavaliers are the best unit in the Realm if 
they are present in great number.  As mentionned above thier main strategy is to surround the 
ennemy and to quickly charge them from everyside creating confusion into the enemy ranks and 
prevent any possible retreat.  Due to this strategy, the Caragous attack and defense is 
increased by a number depending on the number of caragous units compared to the opponent 
army size.  Therefore, the more caragous you have on the field, the more damages they will 
be able to deal and take before dying.</td></tr> 
 
