<tr><th>Name</th><th>Description</th></tr> 
<tr><td align=left valign=top>Catapult:</td><td>The most feared weapon of the world, the catapult 
is used to throw big rocks at the enemy army killing tons of men before they can even think 
about attacking.  Also, with appropriate technology, their projective can be upgraded to 
explosive power bags dealing even more damages to more units.  Another important thing to 
consider is that the catapult itself does not require any “man” to be kept in your army, but 
it is important to keep in mind that operating it is pretty difficult and require five men, 
therefore for every catapult built, five of your soldiers will be affected to its maintenance 
and operation.</td></tr> 
 
<tr><td align=left valign=top>Infantry:</td><td>A normal gnomish unit, the infantry is very cheap 
and can deal some melee damages preventing your catapults from being destroyed.</td></tr> 
 
<tr><td align=left valign=top>Militia:</td><td>The weakest unit of the world, these men are 
basically taken from the population, paid a small fee and brought on the battlefield with a 
spear.  They get no special training, in fact no training at all and are not even protected 
with an armor.  However, because of their cheapness, they can be used when more protection is 
required and because of their short training period, they can be recruited very quickly.</td></tr> 
 
<tr><td align=left valign=top>Rider:</td><td>As the best gnomish melee fighter, these units are 
generally found in most armies and are highly appreciated by gnomes for their strength and 
speed of attack.</td></tr> 
 
<tr><td align=left valign=top>Rock thrower:</td><td>Comparable to the militia, rockthrowers got 
no armor, weak attack and do not require any special training.  Again, the unit disadvantages 
are also positive and allow them to be recruited quickly when needed.</td></tr> 
 
<tr><td align=left valign=top>Balista:</td><td>Another powerful gnomish war machine.  This unit, 
as the catapult, requires many soldiers to operate and maintain, four men will in fact be 
require for this task.  However, it is important to keep in mind that the number of men 
required for the machine to function is not that big compared to its power since not only 
does the machine deal numerous ranged damages, but it also can be used in close combat...</td></tr> 
</table> 
