<tr><td align=left valign=top>Knight:</td><td>Knights are mounted highly trained soldiers, they 
will represent your most precious unit on the battlefield, they got a very good attack 
potential and a very good armor which allows them to resist to powerful ennemy attacks.  
Their horse also allow them to charge the ennemy and, using their lance, to destroy some
enemy units before they can attack.</td></tr> 
 
<tr><td align=left valign=top>Archer:</td><td>These men got a pretty poor defence potential and 
a weak attack power, however their bows allow them to attack before melee fighting therefore 
killing enemy units before these can attack your troops.  Archers will however not be able to 
attack in close combat due to the fact they are not equiped with any short range weapon.</td></tr> 
 
<tr><td align=left valign=top>Infantry:</td><td>These men should make the major parts of your army, 
they are pretty weak, got no range attack and bad defense, but they are really cheap and in 
very high numbers they can kill many ennemy units and take damages and save the more powerful 
units from dying.</td></tr> 
 
<tr><td align=left valign=top>Mounted Archer:</td><td>Another very precious unit, the mounted 
archers are pretty expensive, but they got a range attack and are efficient in close 
combat, their horses also allows them to get to the main battle field very quickly and to 
get an attack advantage over non-riding opponents.</td></tr> 
 
<tr><td align=left valign=top>Pikeman:</td><td>These men got really poor armor and an average 
attack power, however pikemen are required in any good army.  They will become very 
important mostly if your opponnent got a lot of mounted units because, against them, their 
attack power is doubled giving them one of the best attack for humans for a very low cost.</td></tr> 
 
<tr><td align=left valign=top>Heavy Infantry:</td><td>The second best unit in close combat for humans, 
heavy infantry units can defeat most of your opponent forces pretty easily, however, 
they are pretty expensive and your ressource will quickly run low if you train too many 
of them.</td></tr> 
 
