<tr><td align=left valign=top>Shadow Warrior:</td><td>The Shadow Warriors consitute the best unit 
of any orcish army.  Their hiding skill give them a great advantage over other units by the 
simple fact that they can attack without being noticed and receiving no damages in melee 
fighting.  However, if they are detected by enemies, they will die very quickly.  The only 
problem with their hiding skill is that it does not protect from ranged attack, this is due 
to the randomness of the flying arrows which are not armed at a single target.</td></tr> 
 
<tr><td align=left valign=top>Rusher:</td><td>Usually the most common unit in the orc army, the 
rushers are relatively powerful and not very expensive.  The rushers being mounted on wolves, 
they can reach enemy units quickly and make their mount attack if enough wolf master are 
present on the field to help them control their mount (see Wolf Master description for details).</td></tr> 
 
<tr><td align=left valign=top>Slother:</td><td>A very weak unit, the slothers are not powerful and 
got poor defence, but they are very cheap to train and to equip.  These soldiers, like the 
rushers are mounted and will be able to deal short-ranged damages if enough Wolf Masters are 
present on the battlefield (see Wolf Master description for more details).</td></tr> 
 
<tr><td align=left valign=top>Wolf Master:</td><td>Mounted on wolves, these great soldiers are 
very powerful and can give your army a great advantage if enough are found on the field.  
The skills they learned throught their training allow them to get a great control over wolves 
in general and, because of that, can command their mounts (as well as rusher and slother mounts) 
to attack enemies.  Because of the speed of the wolves and that of their attack, their damages 
are dealt in the short-ranged attack phase.  Please note that the amount of damages dealt by 
slother and rusher mounts depend on the relative number of wolf master you have under your 
control.</td></tr> 
 
<tr><td align=left valign=top>Slinger:</td><td>One of the weakest unit in the world, this unit can 
deal some damages to enemies using their sling and, hopefully, kill some soldiers before dying.  
Even if they are really weak, their cost is low manking them a pretty good unit to train.</td></tr> 
 
<tr><td align=left valign=top>Axe Thrower:</td><td>The second long-ranged attack unit of the orcs, 
these men are useful if you want to deal some damages to your enemies quickly in the fight.  
The great advantage of this unit is that it can deal both ranged and melee damages.</td></tr> 
 
